</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C26401DFC32473320A840008A49187CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C82E275638BE83F150DD625D16BEC9B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD959E0EAC379385D41C70B37809C385" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rather distinct because of its densely pubescent indumentum with long weakly appressed hairs, persistent linear bracteoles and generally compact inflorescence. The type is atypical in the sense that it has a relatively long, compound inflorescence.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
